<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1883,2016]" box="[199,1436,1991,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1991,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Benoit" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[329,538,1991,2016]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Xorides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculatus">
<emphasis box="[329,538,1991,2016]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="58">Xorides aciculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the combination of the following characters: body generally
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,152,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
black; vertex wrinkled; antenna subapically sharply angled at a single joint; face reticulate rugose; pronotum rugulose, smooth centrally; epomia present; epicnemial carina absent; propodeum with longitudinal and partly transverse carinae present, tooth-like projections long; fore and middle trochantelli without apical tooth; fore wing with vein 
<emphasis box="[151,201,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">cu-a</emphasis>
basad of 
<emphasis box="[311,384,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
by about 0.4 of its length; first metasomal tergite 1.6× as long as apical width, longitudinally wrinkled, with subapical transverse grooves, dorsal longitudinal carinae present on proximal 0.7; ovipositor about 2.0× length of hind tibia.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3334984/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" startId="2.[151,250,1930,1952]" targetBox="[151,1435,357,1902]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1930,2024]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1930,1952]" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="(Benoit, 1952)" authorityName="Benoit" authorityYear="1952" baseAuthorityName="Benoit" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[280,624,1930,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Xorides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculatus">
<emphasis box="[280,469,1930,1952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Xorides aciculatus</emphasis>
(Benoit, 1952)
</taxonomicName>
, holotype female (scale bar is 0.25 mm): A) frontal view of head; B) lateral view of head; C) dorsal view of propodeum and first metasomal tergite; D) lateral view of mesosoma; E) dorsal view of metasoma; F) fore wing; G) lateral view of apical flagellomeres; H) lateral view of the ovipositor apex; I) type label.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" box="[199,1336,152,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,152,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Re-description.</emphasis>
Female. 
<typeStatus box="[485,589,152,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[605,670,152,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,357,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,378,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xorides aciculatus (Benoit, 1952), holotype female (scale bar is 0.25 mm): A) frontal view of head; B) lateral view of head; C) dorsal view of propodeum and first metasomal tergite; D) lateral view of mesosoma; E) dorsal view of metasoma; F) fore wing; G) lateral view of apical flagellomeres; H) lateral view of the ovipositor apex; I) type label." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3334984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length approximately 12.0 mm. Fore wing 
<quantity box="[1243,1332,152,177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="60" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,260,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,464,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,357,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,378,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xorides aciculatus (Benoit, 1952), holotype female (scale bar is 0.25 mm): A) frontal view of head; B) lateral view of head; C) dorsal view of propodeum and first metasomal tergite; D) lateral view of mesosoma; E) dorsal view of metasoma; F) fore wing; G) lateral view of apical flagellomeres; H) lateral view of the ovipositor apex; I) type label." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3334984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Figs 1A, 1B, 1G</figureCitation>
) depressed, temples narrowed and short behind eyes, covered with sparse short white setae; frons rugulose, with long carina-like projection between antennal sockets (reaching dorsal ocellus); length of the ocellar-ocular distance 0.8× maximum diameter of lateral ocellus; ocelli small, hind ocellus not extended behind eye; temples and vertex wrinkled; occipital carina complete; antenna subapically sharply angled at a single joint, with 23 flagellomeres, 18 
<superScript attach="left" box="[434,447,330,344]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">th</superScript>
flagellomere with three long sensillae; face about 0.6× as long as wide, reticulate rugose, tentorial pits deep; malar space 1.25× basal width of mandible, with indistinct subocular groove; clypeus 0.4× as long as wide, weakly transversely wrinkled proximally and indistinctly rugulose distally, rounded apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,319,440,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[339,534,440,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,357,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,378,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xorides aciculatus (Benoit, 1952), holotype female (scale bar is 0.25 mm): A) frontal view of head; B) lateral view of head; C) dorsal view of propodeum and first metasomal tergite; D) lateral view of mesosoma; E) dorsal view of metasoma; F) fore wing; G) lateral view of apical flagellomeres; H) lateral view of the ovipositor apex; I) type label." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3334984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Figs 1C, 1D, 1F</figureCitation>
) almost glabrous; propleuron rugulose; pronotum swollen apically, rugulose, smooth centrally, epomia distinct; mesoscutum elongate, densely rugulo-punctate, with strong notauli; scutellum rugulo-punctate and postscutellum longitudinally wrinkled; mesopleuron rugulo-punctate anteroventrally, smooth posteriorly; speculum rugulose, epicnemial carina absent; sternaulus indistinct; metapleuron rugulo-punctate; propodeum rugulo-punctate, with longitudinal and partly transverse carinae present, tooth-like projections long; pleural and submetapleural carinae present; spiracles elongate, small.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,252,656,681]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Legs</emphasis>
slender, hind femur 3.1× as long as wide; hind coxae smooth and sparsely punctate, fore and middle tibiae not swollen, narrower than femora; with V-shaped median ventral groove and subapical emargination; fore and middle trochantelli without apical tooth; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,275,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Wings.</emphasis>
Fore wing vein 2 
<emphasis box="[470,521,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">rs-m</emphasis>
long, about 1.2× distance between 2 
<emphasis box="[929,980,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">rs-m</emphasis>
and 2 
<emphasis box="[1048,1104,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">m-cu</emphasis>
; vein 
<emphasis box="[1172,1222,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">cu-a</emphasis>
basad of 
<emphasis box="[1329,1402,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
by about 0.4 of its length; hind wing with distance between distal abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[983,1016,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Cu</emphasis>
1 and 
<emphasis box="[1084,1107,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">M</emphasis>
about as long as vein 
<emphasis box="[1357,1407,800,825]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">cu-a</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,316,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Metasoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[330,512,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1930,1952]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,357,1902]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,378,1902]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Xorides aciculatus (Benoit, 1952), holotype female (scale bar is 0.25 mm): A) frontal view of head; B) lateral view of head; C) dorsal view of propodeum and first metasomal tergite; D) lateral view of mesosoma; E) dorsal view of metasoma; F) fore wing; G) lateral view of apical flagellomeres; H) lateral view of the ovipositor apex; I) type label." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3334984/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Figs 1C, 1E, 1H</figureCitation>
) strongly sculptured; first tergite 1.6× as long as apical width, longitudinally wrinkled, with subapical transverse grooves, dorsal longitudinal carinae present on basal 0.7; second tergite 0.8× as long as apical width, longitudinally wrinkled, with two large basolateral and third central triangular swellings delimited by basolateral and subapical transverse grooves; third tergite 0.6× as long as apical width, with the same sculpture as previous tergite, with only basolateral swellings; fourth tergite aciculate basally; the remaining tergites smooth; ovipositor about 2.0× length of hind tibia, with the apical teeth; ovipositor sheaths densely pubescent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis box="[199,283,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Colour.</emphasis>
Body generally black except face laterally and temples centrally, antennal flagellomeres 10–14, tergites 5–7 apically and propodeal tooth-like projections apically yellow; clypeus reddish; legs generally brownish-black, fore and middle tibiae and tarsi with yellowish marks; pterostigma, three stripes on fore wing and metasoma apically brown; ovipositor sheaths brown, whitish centrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" box="[199,392,1196,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1196,1221]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1232,1257]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Benoit" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[341,508,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Xorides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[341,508,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Xorides similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Benoit" baseAuthorityYear="1952" box="[817,962,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Xorides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculatus">
<emphasis box="[817,962,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">X. aciculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but has more abundant yellow coloration: face centrally and metasomal tergites 1–2 apicolaterally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
